returnValueDescriptions.disabled: If true, the label, input and helper text should be displayed in a disabled state.
returnValueDescriptions.error: If true, the label is displayed in an error state.
returnValueDescriptions.filled: If true, the form element has some value.
returnValueDescriptions.focused: If true, the form element is focused and not disabled.
returnValueDescriptions.onBlur: Callback fired when the form element has lost focus.
returnValueDescriptions.onChange: Callback fired when the form element's value is modified.
returnValueDescriptions.onFocus: Callback fired when the form element receives focus.
returnValueDescriptions.required: If true, the label will indicate that the input is required.
returnValueDescriptions.value: The value of the form element.
